// 4716
[struct_4716]
param=param_879,Fire Sale
param=param_880,- All items in shops around Gielinor that use coins as currency are free of charge.<br><br>- All items purchased from some select shops can be noted, provided the item can be noted at all.<br>   - There will be a new button on select shops which toggles this effect.<br><br>- Shops no longer buy items for gold.
param=param_884,"league_4_relics_large,5"
param=param_1853,"league_4_relics_medium,5"
param=param_1854,"league_4_relics_medium_off,5"
param=param_881,"league_4_relics,5"
param=param_883,"league_4_relics_off,5"
param=param_882,"league_4_relics_tli,5"
param=param_885,2
param=param_1274,struct_4700
param=param_1855,true

// 4717
[struct_4717]
param=param_879,Globetrotter
param=param_880,- You will be given a Globetrotter Pendant, which grants access to the following:<br><br>- Teleports from a fully upgraded Jewellery Box<br><br>- The following teleports from the Portal Nexus:<br><br>   - Annakarl (Demonic Ruins)<br>   - Ape Atoll<br>   - Ape Atoll Dungeon<br>   - Arceuus Library<br>   - Barbarian Outpost<br>   - Barrows<br>   - Battlefront<br>   - Camelot<br>   - Carrallanger (Graveyard of Shadows)<br>   - Catherby<br>   - Draynor Manor<br>   - East Ardougne<br>   - Falador<br>   - Fenkenstrain's Castle<br>   - Fishing Guild<br>   - Ghorrock (Frozen Waste Plateau)<br>   - Grand Exchange<br>   - Harmony Island<br>   - Ice Plateau<br>   - Kharyrll (Canifis)<br>   - Kourend Castle<br>   - Lassar (Ice Mountain)<br>   - Lumbridge<br>   - Lunar Isle<br>   - Mind Altar<br>   - Ourania<br>   - Paddewwa (Edgeville Dungeon)<br>   - Port Khazard<br>   - Salve Graveyard<br>   - Seers' Village<br>   - Senntisten (Digsite)<br>   - Teleport to House<br>   - The Forgotten Cemetery<br>   - Troll Stronghold<br>   - Trollheim<br>   - Varrock<br>   - Watchtower<br>   - Waterbirth Island<br>   - Weiss<br>   - West Ardougne<br>   - Yanille<br><br>- As this Relic gives you an item it must be unlocked at a Bank.
param=param_884,"league_4_relics_large,4"
param=param_1853,"league_4_relics_medium,4"
param=param_1854,"league_4_relics_medium_off,4"
param=param_881,"league_4_relics,4"
param=param_883,"league_4_relics_off,4"
param=param_882,"league_4_relics_tli,4"
param=param_885,1
param=param_1274,struct_4701
param=param_1855,true

// 4718
[struct_4718]
param=param_879,Bloodthirsty
param=param_880,- You are able to get a Slayer Task and cancel a Slayer Task by speaking to a Slayer Master or checking your Slayer status via your Slayer Gem, Helmet, or Ring.<br><br>- Superior Slayer creatures have a 1/25 chance to appear.<br><br>- Superior Slayer creatures will give Slayer points when killed, based on their Slayer level and difficulty.<br><br>- Superior Slayer creatures now have double the number of rolls on the lesser creature's drop table. This does not double the amount of rolls on the Superior Slayer Creature's unique drop table.<br><br>- There is a 25% chance a superior monster will appear as a 'Bloodthirsty' version, with boosted offensive stats. This monster will triple the number of rolls on the lesser creature's non-unique drop table, plus a roll on its own unique drop table. They will also drop guaranteed Clue Scrolls if it is on the superior's drop table.<br><br>- Expeditious and Slaughter Bracelets will no longer consume charges and have a 35% chance to trigger, up from 25%.
param=param_884,"league_4_relics_large,10"
param=param_1853,"league_4_relics_medium,10"
param=param_1854,"league_4_relics_medium_off,10"
param=param_881,"league_4_relics,10"
param=param_883,"league_4_relics_off,10"
param=param_882,"league_4_relics_tli,10"
param=param_885,4
param=param_1274,struct_4702

// 4719
[struct_4719]
param=param_879,Banker's Note
param=param_880,- This item will allow you to note and unnote items anywhere in Gielinor.<br><br>- You can manually use items on the Banker's Note to unnote or note them all, much like a Bank.<br><br>- The 'Activate' option allows you to note and unnote items in one action with a specified quantity. An object must first be used on the Banker's Note in order for this to work.<br><br>- You can customise how many items the Banker's note will note and unnote using the quantity options.
param=param_884,"league_5_relics_large,16"
param=param_1853,"league_5_relics_medium,16"
param=param_1854,"league_5_relics_medium_off,16"
param=param_881,"league_5_relics,16"
param=param_883,"league_5_relics_off,16"
param=param_882,"league_5_relics_tli,16"
param=param_885,5
param=param_1274,struct_4703
param=param_1855,true
param=param_2049,league_bankers_note

// 4720
[struct_4720]
param=param_879,Soul Stealer
param=param_880,- All your attacks have an increased minimum hit (10% of your max hit).<br><br>- Whenever one of your attacks successfully hits, there is a 50% chance that you will restore your Hitpoints and Prayer by 10% of the damage dealt, rounded up.<br><br>- This Relic's restore effect does not work for multi-target attacks or Special Attacks.<br><br>- This Relic's restoration effect will work with the Scythe of Vitur's initial hit, however, it will only work for its secondary hits if those hits have the same target as the initial hit. The Restoration effect will only work on the Venator bow's initial hit.
param=param_884,"league_4_relics_large,17"
param=param_1853,"league_4_relics_medium,17"
param=param_1854,"league_4_relics_medium_off,17"
param=param_881,"league_4_relics,17"
param=param_883,"league_4_relics_off,17"
param=param_882,"league_4_relics_tli,17"
param=param_885,6
param=param_1274,struct_4704

// 4721
[struct_4721]
param=param_879,Weapon Master
param=param_880,- Every 30 seconds, your Special Attack energy is restored by 30% rather than the usual 10%.<br><br>- If you have no Special Attack energy remaining, you sacrifice 25 hitpoints for the special attack instead.<br><br>- Special Attacks are 100% accurate against monsters.<br><br>- Special Attacks have a minimum hit of 20% of your max hit.
param=param_884,"league_4_relics_large,15"
